name Spicy Watermelon Salad
serves 3
note 
  <p>As a starter, the recipe serves twice as many.</p>
  <p>Goes well with baguette.</p>
tags main, starter, salad, vegetarian

# Preparation

- 1.5 kg watermelon
- 500 g Galia melon
Cut off the rind, deseed the flesh and cut into pieces. Refrigerate.
-> melon pieces

- 1 "red chilli"
- 20 g "fresh ginger"
- 1 lime
- 0.5 "red onion"
- 2 tbsp honey
- 1 tsp sesame oil
- 5 tbsp olive oil
- salt
@nodep
Halve, deseed and finely dice the chilli. Peel and finely grate or purée the ginger.
Juice the lime. Cut the onion into thin strips. Whisk everything together, season with
salt and refrigerate.
-> dressing

- 100 g cashews
- 3 tbsp icing sugar
@nodep
Toast the cashews in a dry pan over medium heat until lightly golden. Sprinkle with icing
sugar and heat until the sugar caramelises. Transfer to baking paper, leave to cool and
roughly chop.
-> caramelised cashews

- 1.5 bunches mint
= melon pieces
= dressing
= caramelised cashews
Pour off any juice that has collected from the melon pieces. Finely chop the mint. Toss
the melon, mint and dressing together. Scatter the cashews on top and serve immediately.
